						<div class="postbody">A platformer game should strive for atleast SMB3 or SMW animation, which is in the 15 fps ballpark.  A lot of games tend to animate characters in the 4-8 fps ballpark, with delayed controls to match.  Super Castlevania 4 has that problem.  I actually prefer Dracula X to Super Castlevania 4 because of it's tighter control.</div>

